HEADWORD: Latirostres
<hw>Lat`i*ros"tres</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>latus</ets> broad + <ets>rostrum</ets> beak.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The broad-billed singing birds, such as the
swallows, and their allies.</def>⟦br⟧
